  "issue_number": 57,
  "issue_title": "bug: session_end backfills proposal_ids with all statuses including decided proposals",
  "issue_body": "**Description**\n\nIn `session_end()` inside `src/vouch/sessions.py`, the backfill of `proposal_ids` calls `store.list_proposals()` with no status filter:\n\n`sess.proposal_ids = sorted({p.id for p in store.list_proposals() if p.session_id == sess.id})`\n\n`store.list_proposals()` with no argument returns all proposals regardless of status \u2014 pending, approved, rejected, and decided. This means `proposal_ids` on the session object includes proposals that were already resolved before `session_end` was called, inflating the count stored in the audit log and shown in the session summary.\n\n**Steps to Reproduce**\n\n1. Start a session and file two proposals\n2. Approve one proposal before calling `session_end`\n3. Call `session_end`\n4. Observe: `proposal_ids` includes both the pending and the already-approved proposal \u2014 audit log shows inflated count\n\n**Actual Behavior**\n\n`proposal_ids` includes proposals of all statuses. Audit events and session summaries report inflated proposal counts.\n\n**Expected Behavior**\n\nThe audit log count should correctly reflect only proposals that were still pending at session end, not all proposals ever filed in the session.\n\n**Environment**\n\n- Python 3.11+\n- vouch pre-1.0",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-25T20:59:59.000Z",
